title: SFH on Import and Export (General)(Amendment) Regulation 2013
content_text:
p>
          Following is the transcript of remarks made by the Secretary for Food 
          and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, after attending a public function this 
          morning (March 7): Reporter: Have you assessed whether you have enough support in the 
          Legislative Council for the passage of the new law (Import and Export 
          (General)(Amendment) Regulation 2013) and whether you have set the 
          time limit for it? Secretary for Food and Health: We have noticed that in the recent

week, there have been various opinions, expressed in Hong Kong as well 
          as on the Mainland, regarding our legislative move to restrict the 
          export of infant formula from Hong Kong. In response, I have already, 
          through some Mainland media, made a lot of explanation and 
          clarification. We sincerely hope that through such effort, any 
          misunderstanding, both in Hong Kong as well as on the Mainland, could 
          be clarified because the only aim and objective for the HKSAR 
          Government taking this legislative move is to ensure adequate supply

Government taking this legislative move is to ensure adequate supply 
          of infant formula for Hong Kong parents and their babies. Regarding the necessary completion of the relevant legislative 
          process, we are aware of the fact that there have been different 
          opinions from our Legislative Councillors. In this respect, we will 
          double our effort in our explanatory and lobbying work to the 
          legislators, hoping that they would understand the rationale of this 
          legislative move, which is really something that we are taking as a 
          last measure to ensure the adequate supply of infant formula to Hong
last measure to ensure the adequate supply of infant formula to Hong Kong families. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript.)
